[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND POST-DEPLOYMENT MONITORING ────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated coordinator responses                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active longitudinal-store version                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active source-system versions and pull timestamps    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Multi-stakeholder retention discipline]                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific medical-record retention     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      rules, payer-specific contract retention, and any    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      litigation-hold obligations                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Information-blocking compliance for patient access   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to coordination records                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation as long-time-horizon commitment]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-quarter to multi-year implementation           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Owned jointly by care-team operations, data          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      science, and program leadership                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Attrition rate by patient cohort                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral-completion rate                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Prior-auth-resolution rate                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Transition-of-care follow-up rate                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Medication-reconciliation accuracy                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Open-clinical-loop closure rate                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Source-staleness rate (responses where the           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      latest data was older than the patient assumed)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      flags)                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of high-risk      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      coordination cases                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (care managers, clinical leadership)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tag failure modes (out-of-scope, citation-gap,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      stale-source, conflict-mishandled, advocacy-voice-   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      slip, patient-misled)                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Coordination-protocol revisions driven by review     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      findings                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    coordination-protocol-revision proposals]              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordinator.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-organizational longitudinal store as architectural primitive.** The store integrates EHR data, claims data, payer data, pharmacy data, scheduling data, referral data, and HIE/QHIN data with patient identity resolution and source-confidence stamping. The store is the central data asset; all coordinator value is concentrated in it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Referral, prior-auth, and transition-of-care state machines.** Each is a state machine with stages, time windows, escalation triggers, and resolution paths. The state machines are encoded explicitly and exposed to the LLM through tools.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Patient-advocacy voice as architectural discipline.** The coordinator is on the patient's side. The voice calibration, the willingness to surface friction in plain language, and the avoidance of defensive system-agent register are part of the architecture, enforced through prompt design, output safety, and sampled review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Action-on-behalf-of-patient policy with explicit consent scope.** The boundary between act-on-behalf and route-to-patient is institutionally specified, consent-gated, and operationally enforced.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Source-confidence and freshness stamping as architectural primitive.** Each fact has a source and a freshness; the coordinator surfaces this when relevant. A response built on six-week-old claims data is stamped accordingly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-organizational identity resolution as prerequisite.** Without robust patient-matching across organizations, the longitudinal store has gaps. The deployment plan includes the patient-matching infrastructure (recipe 5.5 patterns).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-stakeholder audit posture.** The coordinator's audit trail is consumed by the patient's care team, the payer (where applicable), compliance, and the patient themselves under information-blocking rules. The audit posture is calibrated for multi-stakeholder consumption with appropriate role-scoped access.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the coordinator is uncertain, when the data is stale, when the conversation drifts toward clinical territory, the response defaults to "let me connect you with your provider's office" or "let me connect you with a care manager."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, attrition, referral-completion, transition-of-care follow-up, prior-auth resolution, citation-coverage, and outcome metrics vary by language, channel, condition complexity, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, and provider footprint complexity. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any source system is unreachable, the coordinator degrades gracefully with stale-data warnings, source-system-status surfacing, and direct routing to human resources. The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
